 [FILES] 23.2 million of 69.7 million Nigerians in the labour market are jobless.  “This was 13.22 per cent less than the number of persons in Q2, 2020. Of this number, those within the age bracket of 25-34 were highest, with 20,091,695 or 28.34 per cent of the labour force.  According to the data, unemployment was worst among youth between 24 and 35 years where 7.5 million or 37 per cent of the number of the demographic group in the labour market were jobless. 
   
Female unemployment was highest among the genders with 35.2 per cent while that of the male was 31.8 per cent during the reference period. The trend is the same for underemployment where 24.2 per cent was reported for females as against males’ 21.8 per cent.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .